Description: Handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.200, 34. Name, Timogenes. His stamps can be with or without the additional A; no other example with Dalios is known.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0561)
